            . I am shopman to Robert Heslep. I saw the prisoner draw the ribbon through the bolt hole, he cut it off; I called out to the other shopman; he ran out, and caught him.</p>
               <p>ROBERT BARFORD. I am shopman also to Mr. Heslep. From information of Braybrook, I ran out and caught the prisoner, and took the ribbon from him; there are seven yards, it is worth four shillings; it is Mr. Heslep's property.</p>
